<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="494" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1440,2043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1476,1502]" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Greek 
<emphasis box="[530,591,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">leuco</emphasis>
(= white) + the Latin 
<emphasis box="[845,960,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">maculatus</emphasis>
(= maculate), referring to the body coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="499" pageId="9" pageNumber="494" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1440,2043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,1548,1574]" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Description of female.</emphasis>
Based on 
<typeStatus box="[575,676,1548,1574]" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">holotype</typeStatus>
, ovigerous female, 
<quantity box="[892,977,1548,1575]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="494" unit="mm" value="7.1">7.1 mm</quantity>
(OMNH-Ar-12233). 
<emphasis box="[1218,1276,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Body</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1291,1358,1548,1575]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1370,1394]" captionTargetBox="[216,1376,192,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[201,1386,181,1346]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Metodius leucomaculatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female, 7.1 mm (OMNH-Ar-12233). Habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683393/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), pereonites 6, 7 with small and medium dorsal projections, respectively; pleonites 1–3 each with dorsal projection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1440,2043]" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1620,1646]" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[279,352,1620,1647]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1370,1394]" captionTargetBox="[216,1376,192,1334]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[201,1386,181,1346]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Metodius leucomaculatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female, 7.1 mm (OMNH-Ar-12233). Habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683393/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[365,379,1620,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,189,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[181,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Metodius leucomaculatus gen. et sp. nov. Holotype, ovigerous female, 7.1 mm (OMNH-Ar-12233). Scales: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5683395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5683395/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">8</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[403,644,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Lateral cephalic lobe</emphasis>
projected anteroventrally. 
<emphasis box="[947,1000,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Eyes</emphasis>
large, 9.9% length of body. 
<emphasis box="[1321,1436,1620,1647]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Antenna 1</emphasis>
somewhat slender; length ratio of peduncular articles 1–3 1:0.55:0.25; accessory flagellum minute, tip with 1 thick and 1 simple setae; primary flagellum with 8 articles, article 1 elongate, each article with several aesthetascs. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Antenna 2</emphasis>
slender, almost same length as antenna 1, with ratio of lengths of peduncular articles 3–5 1:1.85:1.4; flagellum with 10 articles, article 1 long. 
<emphasis box="[557,664,1764,1790]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Mandible</emphasis>
, incisor wide, distal margin with 9–11 denticles; left lacinia mobilis bearing 10 denticles; accessory blades 
<quantity box="[590,648,1800,1826]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="9" pageNumber="494" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
number; palp long, length ratio of palp articles 
<quantity box="[1190,1261,1800,1826]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" metricValueMax="7.62" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="9" pageNumber="494" unit="in" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 in</quantity>
right 1:4.1:4.0, with numerous fine setae on anterior margin and lateral surface and 3 thick setae on tip. 
<emphasis box="[1134,1242,1836,1862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Maxilla 1</emphasis>
, inner plate oval, with single seta on tip; medial margin of outer plate bearing 6 large and ca. 30 small robust setae and many simple setae, dorsal and ventral surfaces covered with fine setae, palp very short. 
<emphasis box="[980,1101,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="494">Maxilliped</emphasis>
, inner plate slightly projected mediodistally, with many plumose setae distally and medially; outer plate rounded, mediodistal margin distinctly serrated, distal margin setose; laterodistal corners of palp articles 1, 2 each bearing single robust seta, article 3 setose mediodistally, article 4 slender, ca. 0.6 times length of article 3.
</paragraph>
